HEADWORD: Hun
<hw>Hun</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>Hunni</ets>, also
<ets>Chunni</ets>, and <ets>Chuni</ets>; cf. AS. <ets>H<?/nas</ets>,
<ets>H<?/ne</ets>, OHG. <ets>H<?/ni</ets>, G. <ets>Hunnen</ets>.]</ety>
<def>One of a warlike nomadic people of Northern Asia who, in the 5th
century, under Atilla, invaded and conquered a great part of
Europe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

